post_text:
Good morning parents/guardians,

I hope you and your family are well. The North Hanover Township School District is currently in the process of preparing for the reopening of our schools in September. In order to meet the specific needs of our community we are gathering input from parents, staff, community stakeholders, municipal leaders, and medical professionals via surveys, a steering committee, and task specific sub-committees. Please complete the Return to School Survey for Parents by Monday, July 13th by clicking on the link below.

Thank you for your continued support and flexibility as we strive to do what is best for all of our students and staff during these challenging times.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc3JaZKL6bwm5TtllE8l7IrWU8OmsSvrvUdbc-anGPCoX28hg/viewform

Sincerely,

Helen Payne
Superintendent
North Hanover Township Schools

Message from the NJDOE:

Dear Parents,

Thank you for your heroic efforts to support your children’s schools and the learning process during closings due to the coronavirus pandemic. The New Jersey Department of Education (Department) continues preparations for the next stages of school opening, and hearing from parents is a Department priority. Please take a few minutes to complete the survey at the following link: NJDOE parent survey. We appreciate receiving your responses by Monday, June 8th.

If you have any questions, please contact the Department’s Office of Civic and Social Engagement at civicandsocial@doe.nj.gov.

https://es.surveymonkey.com/r/V8HZ2MQ

Hello North Hanover families! This week is the Scholastic School Book Fair. If you would not like to send in cash with your child, you can set up an account with Book Fair e-Wallet. You add money, print the receipt then your child will give it to their teacher. Your child will be able to shop for books up to the amount you added. No cash needed!

Here are the links:

Endeavour:
https://bookfairs.scholastic.com/bookfairs/parent-how-it-works.html?webUrl=endeavourschool

CB Lamb:
https://bookfairs.scholastic.com/bookfairs/cptoolkit/homepage.do?method=homepage&url=clarencelambelementarysch

post_text:
Dear C. B. Lamb Parents & Guardians,

This is a friendly reminder that this Thursday, September 5, 2019 from 8:30 am - 10:30 am is "Meet Your Teacher Day!" We are truly excited to meet you and your child. Additionally, we are holding two 30 minute optional sessions in the all-purpose room at C.B. Lamb to go over arrival and dismissal procedures, parent friendly reminders, and other school related information pertaining to this year. If you are unable to attend one of these sessions which are at 9:00 am and 9:30 am, you can access the presentation on C.B. Lamb's Website. Do not hesitate to reach out to our front office if you have any questions at (609) 738 - 2630.

Sincerely,

Dr. Paterson

New student Preschool (3 yr old & 4 yr old) and Kindergarten (5 yr old) registration are now open for children living in North Hanover Township or Joint Base MDL. All programs are a full day with transportation. Registration appointments will be open from February 25, 2019 - May 10, 2019. If your child is currently attending Discovery School, you do not need to register again. If you are unable to register during this time frame there will be a limited summer registration schedule.

Students must be three, four or five years old on or before October 1, 2019.
